snippet: The bailed-out mortgage finance company will turn over a $7 billion dividend to the federal government next month.
abstract: Freddie Mac says it earned $4.6 billion in first quarter, helped by stronger housing market; bailed-out mortgage finance company will pay dividend of $7 billion to Treasury Dept in June.
lead_paragraph: The bailed-out mortgage finance company will turn over a $7 billion dividend to the federal government next month.
